<node id="Ischemia">
  <data key="d0">Ischemia</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A condition characterized by insufficient blood supply to an organ or tissue, which can be static, dynamic, or mixed in TBAD.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-64e4ac484241fa2935c4cb7924488a0b</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836582</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gastrointestinal Ischemia">
  <data key="d0">Gastrointestinal Ischemia</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Ischemia of the gastrointestinal tract caused by TBAD involving the celiac trunk or mesenteric arteries, leading to symptoms like acute abdomen and melena.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-64e4ac484241fa2935c4cb7924488a0b</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836582</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Renal Ischemia">
  <data key="d0">Renal Ischemia</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Ischemia of the kidneys resulting from TBAD involving the renal arteries, presenting with hematuria, anuria, or renal failure.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-64e4ac484241fa2935c4cb7924488a0b</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836582</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Lower Limb Ischemia">
  <data key="d0">Lower Limb Ischemia</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Ischemia of the lower extremities due to TBAD involving the lower limb arteries, characterized by pain, pallor, pulselessness, paresthesia, and paralysis.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-64e4ac484241fa2935c4cb7924488a0b</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836582</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Heart Complication">
  <data key="d0">Heart Complication</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Complications such as aortic valve insufficiency, acute myocardial infarction, or pericardial tamponade, which are rare in TBAD but indicate progression to the ascending aorta.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-64e4ac484241fa2935c4cb7924488a0b</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836582</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Neurological Complication">
  <data key="d0">Neurological Complication</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Complications involving the nervous system, including stroke and spinal cord ischemia, which can arise from TBAD.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-64e4ac484241fa2935c4cb7924488a0b</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836582</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Spinal Cord Ischemia">
  <data key="d0">Spinal Cord Ischemia</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Ischemia of the spinal cord caused by TBAD involving the subclavian artery, great radicular artery, or internal iliac artery, leading to paraplegia and incontinence.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-64e4ac484241fa2935c4cb7924488a0b</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836582</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Great Radicular Artery">
  <data key="d0">Great Radicular Artery</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The most important arterial branch supplying the thoracolumbar spinal cord, typically originating from the left side of the aorta between T8 and L2.&lt;SEP&gt;The great radicular artery (arteria radicularis magna) is a spinal artery whose coverage can lead to paraplegia; approximately 75% originate from the T8-L1 segment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-64e4ac484241fa2935c4cb7924488a0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-591716ddeca1a26bf837c5b70ca9d6db</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836582</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Rupture">
  <data key="d0">Rupture</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">A severe complication of TBAD leading to hemorrhagic shock, characterized by altered mental status, pallor, tachycardia, and hypotension.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-64e4ac484241fa2935c4cb7924488a0b</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836582</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Physical Sign">
  <data key="d0">Physical Sign</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Clinical indicators of TBAD, including limb blood pressure abnormalities, chest signs, abdominal signs, cardiac findings, and neurological deficits.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-64e4ac484241fa2935c4cb7924488a0b</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836582</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Laboratory Examination">
  <data key="d0">Laboratory Examination</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Diagnostic tests including blood routine, D-dimer, and biochemistry used for the differential diagnosis of aortic dissection and identifying comorbidities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-64e4ac484241fa2935c4cb7924488a0b</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836582</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Celiac Trunk">
  <data key="d0">Celiac Trunk</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
  <data key="d2">A major artery in the abdomen that, if involved in TBAD, can cause gastrointestinal ischemia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-64e4ac484241fa2935c4cb7924488a0b</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mesenteric Artery">
  <data key="d0">Mesenteric Artery</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
  <data key="d2">Arteries supplying the intestines that, when affected by TBAD, can lead to gastrointestinal ischemia and bowel necrosis.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-64e4ac484241fa2935c4cb7924488a0b</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Renal Artery">
  <data key="d0">Renal Artery</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
  <data key="d2">Arteries supplying the kidneys; involvement by TBAD can cause hematuria, anuria, or renal failure.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-64e4ac484241fa2935c4cb7924488a0b</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Subclavian Artery">
  <data key="d0">Subclavian Artery</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
  <data key="d2">An artery that, when involved in TBAD, can cause significant blood pressure differences between upper limbs or contribute to spinal cord ischemia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-64e4ac484241fa2935c4cb7924488a0b</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Internal Iliac Artery">
  <data key="d0">Internal Iliac Artery</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
  <data key="d2">The most important distal blood supply source for the spinal cord; involvement by</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-64e4ac484241fa2935c4cb7924488a0b</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Investors">
  <data key="d0">Investors</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Investors are concerned over rising interest rates and regulatory uncertainty, leading to a selloff and a search for safe-haven assets.&lt;SEP&gt;Investors are concerned over rising interest rates and regulatory uncertainty, leading to a market selloff and a shift towards safe-haven assets.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-64e4ac484241fa2935c4cb7924488a0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c6c2b152c9eaada554199a5037bc57d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e562c0cde0c973324835a564611458a5</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sedation And Analgesia">
  <data key="d0">Sedation And Analgesia</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A medical intervention used to calm the patient, relieve pain, and reduce sympathetic nerve excitement to prevent increases in heart rate and blood pressure. Opioids like Pethidine or Morphine are commonly used.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-605ec9a012188bcab7dd557b160b0311</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Blood Pressure Control">
  <data key="d0">Blood Pressure Control</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Blood Pressure Control involves maintaining the mean arterial pressure around 100 mmHg during stent deployment to ensure precise anchoring.&lt;SEP&gt;A therapeutic strategy aimed at reducing systolic blood pressure to 100-130 mmHg and maintaining mean arterial pressure at 60-70 mmHg, while ensuring minimum effective end-organ perfusion (urine output &gt;30 ml/h).</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-605ec9a012188bcab7dd557b160b0311&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e562c0cde0c973324835a564611458a5</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Heart Rate Control">
  <data key="d0">Heart Rate Control</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A therapeutic strategy targeting a heart rate of 60-80 beats/min to reduce left ventricular contractility and contraction rate, preventing reflexive catecholamine release and aortic wall shear stress.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-605ec9a012188bcab7dd557b160b0311</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pethidine">
  <data key="d0">Pethidine</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">An opioid medication used for sedation and analgesia, typically administered intravenously at 100 mg, with repeat dosing every 6-8 hours if necessary.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-605ec9a012188bcab7dd557b160b0311</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Morphine">
  <data key="d0">Morphine</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">An opioid medication used for sedation and analgesia, typically administered intravenously at 5-10 mg, with repeat dosing every 6-8 hours if necessary.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-605ec9a012188bcab7dd557b160b0311</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Beta Receptor Blockers">
  <data key="d0">Beta Receptor Blockers</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Medications such as Metoprolol and Esmolol used as foundational intravenous drug therapy for blood pressure control.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-605ec9a012188bcab7dd557b160b0311</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Alpha Receptor Blockers">
  <data key="d0">Alpha Receptor Blockers</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Medications such as Urapidil used as foundational intravenous drug therapy for blood pressure control.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-605ec9a012188bcab7dd557b160b0311</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Calcium Channel Blockers">
  <data key="d0">Calcium Channel Blockers</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Medications such as Nicardipine and Diltiazem used in combination when initial blood pressure control is ineffective.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-605ec9a012188bcab7dd557b160b0311</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Acute Or Subacute TBAD">
  <data key="d0">Acute Or Subacute TBAD</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Acute or subacute Type B Aortic Dissection, a medical condition requiring initial drug therapy and potential surgical or endovascular intervention depending on complexity.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-605ec9a012188bcab7dd557b160b0311</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Acute Complex TBAD">
  <data key="d0">Acute Complex TBAD</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A severe form of Type B Aortic Dissection requiring early surgical intervention on top of sufficient medical therapy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-605ec9a012188bcab7dd557b160b0311</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Acute Non-Complex TBAD">
  <data key="d0">Acute Non-Complex TBAD</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A form of Type B Aortic Dissection with lower short-term mortality under medical therapy, but potential long-term benefits from endovascular treatment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-605ec9a012188bcab7dd557b160b0311</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Acute High-Risk TBAD">
  <data key="d0">Acute High-Risk TBAD</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A subgroup of acute non-complex TBAD with high-risk factors, where medical therapy alone often leads to poor prognosis, making TEVAR the recommended first choice.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-605ec9a012188bcab7dd557b160b0311</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="TEVAR">
  <data key="d0">TEVAR</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Thoracic Endovascular Aortic Repair, a preferred endovascular treatment that uses an endograft to cover the primary tear, redirect blood to the true lumen, promote false lumen thrombosis, and improve aortic remodeling.&lt;SEP&gt;Thoracic Endovascular Aortic Repair, a treatment method with lower perioperative mortality and complication rates compared to open surgery in chronic TBAD, but higher reintervention and rupture risks.&lt;SEP&gt;Thoracic Endovascular Aortic Repair, a surgical method used to treat various aortic conditions, including TBAD, penetrating ulcers, and traumatic dissections.&lt;SEP&gt;Thoracic Endovascular Aortic Repair (TEVAR) is a surgical method for TBAD. It is associated with complications like endoleaks, SINE, RTAD, and stroke, and involves the deployment of stent grafts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-605ec9a012188bcab7dd557b160b0311&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d7f57c2b991109e54368f11500570de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fab34d9740517cca09be688eae0a7dda&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a9e9b35bcbdba3ac4b13dbf19b5e0877</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="INSTEAD Study">
  <data key="d0">INSTEAD Study</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">A research study with 5-year follow-up results showing that endovascular treatment provides better aortic remodeling and lower long-term aortic-related adverse event risks compared to drug therapy alone for non-complex TBAD.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-605ec9a012188bcab7dd557b160b0311</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Endograft">
  <data key="d0">Endograft</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A腔内移植物used in TEVAR to cover the primary tear entry and reshape the true lumen.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-605ec9a012188bcab7dd557b160b0311</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="General Anesthesia">
  <data key="d0">General Anesthesia</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">General Anesthesia is the preferred anesthesia method for surgeries requiring significant blood pressure control, though local anesthesia is an alternative for high-risk or hemodynamically unstable patients.&lt;SEP&gt;The preferred anesthesia method for TE</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-605ec9a012188bcab7dd557b160b0311&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e562c0cde0c973324835a564611458a5</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Intramural Hematoma">
  <data key="d0">Intramural Hematoma</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A condition that cannot be ruled out even with a negative D-dimer result, assessable via non-contrast CT before injecting contrast agents.&lt;SEP&gt;A special type of TBAD characterized by a circular or crescent-shaped hematoma in the aortic media.&lt;SEP&gt;An acute aortic condition characterized by a circular or crescent-shaped high-density shadow in the aortic media and wall thickening (&gt;5 mm), without an obvious intimal tear or false lumen.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5d7f57c2b991109e54368f11500570de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1cfaf9e1c9e4a4c49d23e85f0cbdc90c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a9e9b35bcbdba3ac4b13dbf19b5e0877</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Penetrating Ulcer">
  <data key="d0">Penetrating Ulcer</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A condition that cannot be excluded even with a negative D-dimer result.&lt;SEP&gt;An atherosclerotic plaque ulcer that penetrates the internal elastic membrane into the aortic media, often associated with intramural hematoma and high risk of rupture if deep.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5d7f57c2b991109e54368f11500570de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1cfaf9e1c9e4a4c49d23e85f0cbdc90c</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Traumatic Dissection">
  <data key="d0">Traumatic Dissection</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A type of TBAD caused by trauma, considered an acute emergency often combined with multiple injuries and having a high 24-hour mortality rate.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5d7f57c2b991109e54368f11500570de</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Iatrogenic Dissection">
  <data key="d0">Iatrogenic Dissection</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A rare type of dissection caused by medical procedures such as catheter-related coronary interventions, cardiac surgery, or aortic valve replacement.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5d7f57c2b991109e54368f11500570de</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pregnancy">
  <data key="d0">Pregnancy</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A physiological state that, when combined with TBAD, requires specialized treatment strategies based on gestational age and maternal/fetal emergency status.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5d7f57c2b991109e54368f11500570de</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Takayasu Arteritis">
  <data key="d0">Takayasu Arteritis</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A large vessel vasculitis that can rarely lead to TBAD, requiring inflammation control alongside surgical or endovascular treatment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5d7f57c2b991109e54368f11500570de</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Endoleak">
  <data key="d0">Endoleak</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A common complication after TEVAR where blood continues to flow into the false lumen through various pathways, with Proximal Type I being the most common.&lt;SEP&gt;Endoleak refers to the continued flow of blood into the false lumen through various pathways, such as between the stent graft and aortic wall, intercostal artery backflow, branch artery involvement, stent fabric damage or leakage, and unclosed distal tears. Type I endoleak at the proximal end is the most common.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5d7f57c2b991109e54368f11500570de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fab34d9740517cca09be688eae0a7dda</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="MDT">
  <data key="d0">MDT</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Multi-disciplinary team, a collaborative group of specialists required to assess and manage traumatic TBAD combined with multiple injuries.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5d7f57c2b991109e54368f11500570de</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Unenhanced CT">
  <data key="d0">Unenhanced CT</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A computed tomography scan without contrast, noted as the clearest imaging method for displaying intramural hematoma.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5d7f57c2b991109e54368f11500570de</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Contrast-Enhanced CT">
  <data key="d0">Contrast-Enhanced CT</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A computed tomography scan with contrast, used to show contrast agent extravasation penetrating calcified plaques in penetrating ulcers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5d7f57c2b991109e54368f11500570de</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
