<node id="Beta-blockers">
  <data key="d0">Beta-blockers</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Beta-blockers are the most commonly used basic antihypertensive drugs for postoperative TBAD patients, which may delay residual dissection expansion, reduce aortic-related events, and improve long-term survival.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4c6c2b152c9eaada554199a5037bc57d</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Angiotensin Converting Enzyme Inhibitors">
  <data key="d0">Angiotensin Converting Enzyme Inhibitors</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Angiotensin Converting Enzyme Inhibitors are antihypertensive drugs that can be combined with beta-blockers under specialist guidance when the latter's blood pressure-lowering effect is inadequate.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4c6c2b152c9eaada554199a5037bc57d</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Angiotensin II Receptor Antagonists">
  <data key="d0">Angiotensin II Receptor Antagonists</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Angiotensin II Receptor Antagonists are antihypertensive drugs that can be combined with beta-blockers under specialist guidance when the latter's blood pressure-lowering effect is inadequate.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4c6c2b152c9eaada554199a5037bc57d</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dihydropyridine Calcium Channel Blockers">
  <data key="d0">Dihydropyridine Calcium Channel Blockers</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Dihydropyridine Calcium Channel Blockers are antihypertensive drugs that can be combined with beta-blockers under specialist guidance when the latter's blood pressure-lowering effect is inadequate.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4c6c2b152c9eaada554199a5037bc57d</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="IRAD">
  <data key="d0">IRAD</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The International Registry of Acute Aortic Dissection (IRAD) is an international registry that collects data on acute aortic dissection, reporting an average patient age of 63.1 years and a male predominance of about 65%.&lt;SEP&gt;IRAD (International Registry of Acute Aortic Dissection) is a research organization that reported a 30.6% 5-year reintervention rate after endovascular treatment for TBAD.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4c6c2b152c9eaada554199a5037bc57d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bdff5950e030006d07ec6e2731df6a7</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="RTAD">
  <data key="d0">RTAD</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Retrograde type A dissection (RTAD) is a severe complication that can be caused by proximal SINE, spontaneous ascending aortic new tears from disease progression, or iatrogenic injury during procedures. It requires immediate management as a type A dissection.&lt;SEP&gt;RTAD (Retrograde Type A Dissection) is one of the indications for reintervention in TBAD patients.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4c6c2b152c9eaada554199a5037bc57d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fab34d9740517cca09be688eae0a7dda</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Open Surgery">
  <data key="d0">Open Surgery</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A surgical method characterized by high trauma and high perioperative complication and mortality rates, currently not the first choice for non-hereditary connective tissue disease acute or subacute TBAD patients.&lt;SEP&gt;Open surgery is a treatment method used for reintervention in TBAD patients.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4c6c2b152c9eaada554199a5037bc57d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a9e9b35bcbdba3ac4b13dbf19b5e0877</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated To Fudan University">
  <data key="d0">Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated To Fudan University</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated To Fudan University is a medical institution where experts Chen Zhong, Dong Zhihui, Fu Weiguo, and Zhou Min participated in the consensus writing and discussion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4c6c2b152c9eaada554199a5037bc57d</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
