<node id="Zone 0">
  <data key="d0">Zone 0</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Zone 0 is an anatomical region of the aorta, serving as the starting point for the anatomical zoning system.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09fc3eadb498cd1f3a3ba55ebba9b9ef</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Zone 5">
  <data key="d0">Zone 5</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Zone 5 extends from the midpoint of the descending thoracic aorta (approximately T6 level) to the proximal opening of the celiac trunk.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09fc3eadb498cd1f3a3ba55ebba9b9ef</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Zone 6">
  <data key="d0">Zone 6</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Zone 6 extends from the proximal opening of the celiac trunk to the proximal opening of the superior mesenteric artery.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09fc3eadb498cd1f3a3ba55ebba9b9ef</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Zone 7">
  <data key="d0">Zone 7</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Zone 7 extends from the proximal opening of the superior mesenteric artery to the proximal opening of the high renal artery.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09fc3eadb498cd1f3a3ba55ebba9b9ef</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Zone 8">
  <data key="d0">Zone 8</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Zone 8 extends from the proximal opening of the high renal artery to the distal opening of the low renal artery.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09fc3eadb498cd1f3a3ba55ebba9b9ef</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Zone 9">
  <data key="d0">Zone 9</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Zone 9 extends from the distal opening of the low renal artery to the aortic bifurcation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09fc3eadb498cd1f3a3ba55ebba9b9ef</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Zone 10">
  <data key="d0">Zone 10</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Zone 10 extends from the aortic bifurcation to the common iliac artery bifurcation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09fc3eadb498cd1f3a3ba55ebba9b9ef</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Zone 11">
  <data key="d0">Zone 11</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Zone 11 corresponds to the external iliac artery segment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09fc3eadb498cd1f3a3ba55ebba9b9ef</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Zone 12">
  <data key="d0">Zone 12</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Zone 12 refers to the region distal to the external iliac artery.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09fc3eadb498cd1f3a3ba55ebba9b9ef</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Type A Dissection">
  <data key="d0">Type A Dissection</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Type A dissection is an anatomical classification where the primary tear originates in Zone 0, with distal extent indicated by zone number.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09fc3eadb498cd1f3a3ba55ebba9b9ef</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Type B Dissection">
  <data key="d0">Type B Dissection</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Type B dissection (TBAD) is an anatomical classification where the primary tear originates in Zone 1 or distally, with naming including proximal and distal extent.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09fc3eadb498cd1f3a3ba55ebba9b9ef</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836583</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Type I Dissection">
  <data key="d0">Type I Dissection</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Type I dissection is an anatomical classification for aortic dissections where the primary tear location is indeterminate, often involving Zone 0.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09fc3eadb498cd1f3a3ba55ebba9b9ef</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Anatomical Classification">
  <data key="d0">Anatomical Classification</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Anatomical Classification is a refined method for categorizing aortic dissections based on the origin of the primary tear and the zones of involvement, aiding in risk stratification, treatment, and prognosis.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09fc3eadb498cd1f3a3ba55ebba9b9ef</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="American Heart Association">
  <data key="d0">American Heart Association</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The American Heart Association (AHA) is an organization that published guidelines in 2010 recommending a specific staging method for TBAD.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09fc3eadb498cd1f3a3ba55ebba9b9ef</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="European Society of Cardiology">
  <data key="d0">European Society of Cardiology</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The European Society of Cardiology (ESC) is an organization that published guidelines in 2014 recommending a specific staging method for TBAD, which was later adopted by the consensus.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09fc3eadb498cd1f3a3ba55ebba9b9ef</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Society for Vascular Surgery">
  <data key="d0">Society for Vascular Surgery</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Society for Vascular Surgery (SVS) is an organization that recommended adopting the ESC guideline staging method in 2020.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09fc3eadb498cd1f3a3ba55ebba9b9ef</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Subacute Phase">
  <data key="d0">Subacute Phase</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Subacute Phase is a staging period for TBAD defined by onset time between 14 and 90 days, as recommended by the ESC guidelines.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09fc3eadb498cd1f3a3ba55ebba9b9ef</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="AD">
  <data key="d0">AD</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">AD, or Acute Aortic Dissection, is a cardiovascular condition with an annual incidence of 2.6-6.0 per 100,000 in Western countries, showing higher rates in winter and spring and lowest in summer.&lt;SEP&gt;Aortic Dissection, a medical condition suspected in patients with chest pain, diagnosed and evaluated using various laboratory and imaging methods.&lt;SEP&gt;AD (Aortic Dissection) is a medical condition diagnosed using various imaging and diagnostic methods, requiring immediate medical treatment upon diagnosis.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1cfaf9e1c9e4a4c49d23e85f0cbdc90c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bdff5950e030006d07ec6e2731df6a7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94cd3fdd49a94275f6f089e8593f1e2e</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="D-Dimer">
  <data key="d0">D-Dimer</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">A laboratory test indicator that, when elevated or rapidly increasing, increases the likelihood of AD; serves as an exclusion indicator for acute AD but cannot rule out penetrating ulcers or intramural hematomas if negative.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1cfaf9e1c9e4a4c49d23e85f0cbdc90c</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pulmonary Embolism">
  <data key="d0">Pulmonary Embolism</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A medical condition that must be differentiated from AD when D-dimer levels are elevated.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1cfaf9e1c9e4a4c49d23e85f0cbdc90c</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Transthoracic Echocardiography">
  <data key="d0">Transthoracic Echocardiography</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A portable and widely available imaging method for diagnosing AD by detecting the intimal flap, though it has lower sensitivity for TBAD and is limited by patient body habitus and lung issues.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1cfaf9e1c9e4a4c49d23e85f0cbdc90c</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Transesophageal Echocardiography">
  <data key="d0">Transesophageal Echocardiography</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">An invasive imaging method that overcomes TTE limitations, achieving 99% sensitivity and 89% specificity for AD, but carries risks for acute AD patients without general anesthesia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1cfaf9e1c9e4a4c49d23e85f0cbdc90c</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="CTA">
  <data key="d0">CTA</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The first-choice imaging method for suspected AD patients, characterized by wide availability, rapid acquisition, high sensitivity and specificity, and high spatial resolution.&lt;SEP&gt;CTA is a diagnostic imaging method for AD, compared to which MRI has stronger soft tissue resolution and similar diagnostic efficiency.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1cfaf9e1c9e4a4c49d23e85f0cbdc90c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94cd3fdd49a94275f6f089e8593f1e2e</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="MRI">
  <data key="d0">MRI</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The preferred alternative imaging method for patients with iodine allergy, hyperthyroidism, renal insufficiency, or pregnancy, offering strong soft tissue resolution but requiring a longer scan time.&lt;SEP&gt;MRI is the preferred alternative examination for pregnant women in the first 3 months of gestation or patients with relative or absolute contraindications to CTA. It has similar diagnostic efficiency for AD as CTA, stronger soft tissue resolution, and can qualify or quantify functional parameters, but has a long scan time and is unsuitable for unstable patients or those with implants or claustrophobia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1cfaf9e1c9e4a4c49d23e85f0cbdc90c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94cd3fdd49a94275f6f089e8593f1e2e</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Intimal Flap">
  <data key="d0">Intimal Flap</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A structural feature in aortic dissection that must be identified to distinguish the true and false lumens, detectable by TTE and TEE.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1cfaf9e1c9e4a4c49d23e85f0cbdc90c</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Iliac Artery">
  <data key="d0">Iliac Artery</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
  <data key="d2">Bilateral arteries evaluated during imaging for their diameter, dissection involvement, and degree of distortion as access vessels for endovascular therapy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1cfaf9e1c9e4a4c49d23e85f0cbdc90c</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Local Anesthesia">
  <data key="d0">Local Anesthesia</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Local Anesthesia is an alternative anesthesia method for high-risk patients that also facilitates intraoperative neurological function monitoring.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e562c0cde0c973324835a564611458a5</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Stent Oversizing Rate">
  <data key="d0">Stent Oversizing Rate</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Stent Oversizing Rate refers to the degree of stent expansion required to ensure radial support and tight apposition against the aortic wall while avoiding endoleaks or new intimal tears.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e562c0cde0c973324835a564611458a5</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Balloon Post-Dilation">
  <data key="d0">Balloon Post-Dilation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Balloon Post-Dilation is a procedure that should be avoided as much as possible during aortic stenting to prevent complications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e562c0cde0c973324835a564611458a5</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Aortic Angiography">
  <data key="d0">Aortic Angiography</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Aortic Angiography involves segmented imaging of the aorta using specific angles and levels to assess blood supply, true lumen wire path, and branch vessels.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e562c0cde0c973324835a564611458a5</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Femoral Artery">
  <data key="d0">Femoral Artery</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The Femoral Artery is the preferred access vessel for endovascular interventions, selected based on preoperative imaging of its diameter and tortuosity.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e562c0cde0c973324835a564611458a5</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Proximal Anchoring Zone Extension">
  <data key="d0">Proximal Anchoring Zone Extension</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Proximal Anchoring Zone Extension is a set of techniques used for patients with insufficient or poor proximal anchoring zones (&lt;1.5 cm) or left subclavian artery involvement.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e562c0cde0c973324835a564611458a5</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Left Subclavian Artery">
  <data key="d0">Left Subclavian Artery</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The Left Subclavian Artery is a branch vessel that, if directly covered due to insufficient anchoring, poses risks of neurological complications and subclavian steal syndrome.&lt;SEP&gt;The left subclavian artery is a blood vessel that can be covered during procedures, and its preservation or reconstruction is recommended to prevent paraplegia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e562c0cde0c973324835a564611458a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-591716ddeca1a26bf837c5b70ca9d6db</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Branched Stent Technology">
  <data key="d0">Branched Stent Technology</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Branched Stent Technology uses forward or reverse blood flow branch stents, with single branch stents showing a 97% technical success rate and 93% patency rate in domestic studies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e562c0cde0c973324835a564611458a5</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fenestration Technology">
  <data key="d0">Fenestration Technology</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Fenestration Technology includes in-situ and ex-vivo fenestration to restore branch vessel flow, requiring precise deployment and intraoperative brain protection.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e562c0cde0c973324835a564611458a5</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Parallel Stent Technology">
  <data key="d0">Parallel Stent Technology</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Parallel Stent Technology, evolved from chimney, periscope, and sandwich techniques, uses commercialized stents but carries a higher risk of Type Ia endoleaks.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e562c0cde0c973324835a564611458a5</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hybrid Surgery">
  <data key="d0">Hybrid Surgery</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Hybrid Surgery uses extra-anatomical or anatomical bypass methods to extend the proximal anchoring zone, potentially avoiding open chest procedures or cardiopulmonary bypass.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e562c0cde0c973324835a564611458a5</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Type Ia Endoleak">
  <data key="d0">Type Ia Endoleak</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Type Ia Endoleak is a complication risk associated with parallel stent technology, where a gap between the branch and main stent causes leakage, increasing with more branch stents.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e562c0cde0c973324835a564611458a5</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Type I Endoleak">
  <data key="d0">Type I Endoleak</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Type I endoleak is the most common type of endoleak, primarily caused by an excessively short landing zone or poor apposition between the stent graft and the aortic wall, allowing blood to enter the primary tear from the gap.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fab34d9740517cca09be688eae0a7dda</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Stent Graft">
  <data key="d0">Stent Graft</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A stent graft is a medical device used in endovascular repair. Its apposition with the aortic wall and sizing (oversizing ratio) are critical factors in preventing complications like endoleaks and SINE.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fab34d9740517cca09be688eae0a7dda</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="SINE">
  <data key="d0">SINE</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Stent graft-induced new entry (SINE) is an important complication after TEVAR in TBAD patients, defined as a new tear occurring at the contact area between the stent ends and the aorta, excluding natural disease progression or endovascular operational injuries.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fab34d9740517cca09be688eae0a7dda</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Proximal SINE">
  <data key="d0">Proximal SINE</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Proximal SINE occurs at the proximal end of the stent and often develops into retrograde type A dissection (RTAD), one of the most severe complications post-TEVAR with a mortality rate up to 37.1%.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fab34d9740517cca09be688eae0a7dda</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Distal SINE">
  <data key="d0">Distal SINE</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Distal SINE occurs at the distal end of the stent, with an incidence of about 7.9%, being more common in chronic TBAD. It is closely related to the stent oversizing ratio and is often discovered during imaging follow-up 12-36 months post-operation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fab34d9740517cca09be688eae0a7dda</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Petticoat Technique">
  <data key="d0">Petticoat Technique</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Petticoat technique involves implanting a bare stent distal to the proximal covered stent to expand the true lumen, allow blood flow into visceral arteries, and provide support for the thoracoabdominal aortic intima, potentially reducing distal SINE risk.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fab34d9740517cca09be688eae0a7dda</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Distal Restrictive Stent Technique">
  <data key="d0">Distal Restrictive Stent Technique</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The distal restrictive stent technique involves deploying a small-caliber bare or covered stent with high radial force distally to reduce the oversizing ratio of the distal covered stent, potentially lowering the risk of distal SINE.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fab34d9740517cca09be688eae0a7dda</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Stroke">
  <data key="d0">Stroke</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">A major complication of the new techniques, potentially caused by atheromatous plaque detachment, air embolism, or loss of supra-aortic branch vessels.&lt;SEP&gt;Stroke is defined as focal or widespread neurological impairment lasting&lt;SEP&gt;Stroke is a potential complication whose risk can be reduced by preventing associated risk factors.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fab34d9740517cca09be688eae0a7dda&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a9e9b35bcbdba3ac4b13dbf19b5e0877&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-591716ddeca1a26bf837c5b70ca9d6db</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sino-RAD">
  <data key="d0">Sino-RAD</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Sino-RAD is a domestic aortic dissection registry study in China, reporting an average patient age of 51.8 years, which is about 10 years lower than in Western countries.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bdff5950e030006d07ec6e2731df6a7</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hypertension">
  <data key="d0">Hypertension</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Hypertension is a major risk factor for TBAD that increases aortic wall stress and shear stress. It is highly prevalent in TBAD patients, with 80.9% in IRAD data and 66.2% in domestic studies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bdff5950e030006d07ec6e2731df6a7</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Atherosclerosis">
  <data key="d0">Atherosclerosis</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Atherosclerosis is a risk factor for TBAD, commonly seen in elderly patients with hypertension, hyperlipidemia, and smoking, leading to degenerative changes and ulcers in the aortic wall.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bdff5950e030006d07ec6e2731df6a7</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Marfan Syndrome">
  <data key="d0">Marfan Syndrome</data>
  <data key="d1">disease</data>
  <data key="d2">Marfan Syndrome is the most common hereditary connective tissue disease causing aortic wall structural abnormalities in TBAD. Its diagnosis requires the revised Ghent criteria, combining clinical features, family history, and genetic testing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bdff5950e030006d07ec6e2731df6a7</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Revised Ghent Criteria">
  <data key="d0">Revised Ghent Criteria</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Revised Ghent Criteria is the diagnostic standard for Marfan Syndrome, requiring a comprehensive assessment of clinical features, family history, and genetic test results.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bdff5950e030006d07ec6e2731df6a7</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fibrillin-1 Gene">
  <data key="d0">Fibrillin-1 Gene</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">A mutation in the Fibrillin-1 gene alone is insufficient to establish a diagnosis of Marfan Syndrome.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bdff5950e030006d07ec6e2731df6a7</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Loeys-Dietz Syndrome">
  <data key="d0">Loeys-Dietz Syndrome</data>
  <data key="d1">disease</data>
  <data key="d2">Loeys-Dietz Syndrome is a genetic disease characterized by heterozygous mutations in the transforming growth factor-β receptor 1 or 2 subunits, presenting with a triad of hypertelorism, bifid uvula or cleft palate, and arterial tortuosity.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bdff5950e030006d07ec6e2731df6a7</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Transforming Growth Factor-β Receptor">
  <data key="d0">Transforming Growth Factor-β Receptor</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Heterozygous mutations in the transforming growth factor-β receptor 1 or 2 subunits are the characteristic cause of Loeys-Dietz Syndrome.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bdff5950e030006d07ec6e2731df6a7</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome">
  <data key="d0">Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome</data>
  <data key="d1">disease</data>
  <data key="d2">Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome is caused by mutations in the COL3A1 gene encoding type III collagen, primarily causing dissection or rupture of medium arteries, with aortic involvement also reported.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bdff5950e030006d07ec6e2731df6a7</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="COL3A1 Gene">
  <data key="d0">COL3A1 Gene</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The COL3A1 gene encodes type III collagen, and its mutation leads to Ehlers-Danlos Syndrome.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bdff5950e030006d07ec6e2731df6a7</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Angiography">
  <data key="d0">Angiography</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Angiography was once considered the "gold standard" for AD diagnosis but is no longer a routine diagnostic method due to being invasive. It still has advantages in dynamically displaying branch arteries and blood flow direction.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-94cd3fdd49a94275f6f089e8593f1e2e</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Intravascular Ultrasound">
  <data key="d0">Intravascular Ultrasound</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Intravascular ultrasound can display the 3D structure of the aortic lumen in real-time dynamically. It is mainly used for intraoperative guidance and helps distinguish true and false lumens in complex TBAD, especially when the true lumen is completely compressed.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-94cd3fdd49a94275f6f089e8593f1e2e</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="TEE">
  <data key="d0">TEE</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">TEE (Transesophageal Echocardiography) is a diagnostic method for AD, with lower sensitivity and specificity for AD diagnosis compared to intravascular ultrasound.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-94cd3fdd49a94275f6f089e8593f1e2e</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="2010 AHA Guidelines">
  <data key="d0">2010 AHA Guidelines</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The 2010 AHA Guidelines proposed high-risk predisposing factors, pain manifestations, and signs for suspected AD in patients with acute chest pain.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-94cd3fdd49a94275f6f089e8593f1e2e</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="High-Risk TBAD">
  <data key="d0">High-Risk TBAD</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">High-Risk TBAD refers to TBAD patients with any high-risk factor such as intractable pain, uncontrolled hypertension, bloody pleural effusion, aortic diameter &gt;40 mm, false lumen diameter &gt;22 mm, perfusion deficit found on imaging, primary tear on the lesser curvature, or readmission.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-94cd3fdd49a94275f6f089e8593f1e2e</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Intractable Pain">
  <data key="d0">Intractable Pain</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Intractable pain is defined as severe pain persisting for &gt;12 hours despite adequate antihypertensive, analgesic, and anxiolytic treatment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-94cd3fdd49a94275f6f089e8593f1e2e</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Uncontrolled Hypertension">
  <data key="d0">Uncontrolled Hypertension</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Uncontrolled hypertension is defined as persistent hypertension for &gt;12 hours despite the administration of &gt;3 different types of antihypertensive drugs at maximum recommended or tolerated doses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-94cd3fdd49a94275f6f089e8593f1e2e</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Acute Kidney Injury Network Staging Scale">
  <data key="d0">Acute Kidney Injury Network Staging Scale</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Acute Kidney Injury Network Staging Scale (AKIN) is recommended for evaluating patients with acute kidney injury, particularly in the context of renal perfusion deficits.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-94cd3fdd49a94275f6f089e8593f1e2e</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Modified Rankin Scale">
  <data key="d0">Modified Rankin Scale</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Modified Rankin Scale is a method used for the evaluation of stroke in patients.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-94cd3fdd49a94275f6f089e8593f1e2e</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Modified Tarlov Scoring System">
  <data key="d0">Modified Tarlov Scoring System</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Modified Tarlov Scoring System is used for the evaluation of spinal cord injury in patients.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-94cd3fdd49a94275f6f089e8593f1e2e</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Radionuclide Renography">
  <data key="d0">Radionuclide Renography</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Radionuclide</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-94cd3fdd49a94275f6f089e8593f1e2e</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836584</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Proximal Anchor Zone Extension">
  <data key="d0">Proximal Anchor Zone Extension</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A technique used to extend the proximal anchor zone without sternotomy, aortic cross-clamping, cardiopulmonary bypass, or hypothermic circulatory arrest.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9b35bcbdba3ac4b13dbf19b5e0877</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Anatomical Bypass">
  <data key="d0">Anatomical Bypass</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A bypass method from the ascending aorta to the brachiocephalic vessels requiring sternotomy but without aortic cross-clamping and cardiopulmonary bypass.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9b35bcbdba3ac4b13dbf19b5e0877</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Endovascular Treatment">
  <data key="d0">Endovascular Treatment</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A minimally invasive treatment that can be performed in stages or simultaneously with open surgery, reducing trauma and providing an alternative for patients who cannot tolerate open surgery.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9b35bcbdba3ac4b13dbf19b5e0877</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Informed Consent">
  <data key="d0">Informed Consent</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A mandatory ethical requirement ensuring patients and their families are fully informed before undergoing new surgical techniques.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9b35bcbdba3ac4b13dbf19b5e0877</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Stent Elephant Trunk Surgery">
  <data key="d0">Stent Elephant Trunk Surgery</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A surgical procedure applicable to TBAD caused by hereditary connective tissue diseases, used for patients with aortic root or ascending aorta diseases.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9b35bcbdba3ac4b13dbf19b5e0877</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Distal Tear">
  <data key="d0">Distal Tear</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Secondary tears in the dissecting intima that usually serve as exits for the false lumen, typically not treated during acute or subacute phases after proximal tear exclusion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9b35bcbdba3ac4b13dbf19b5e0877</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Visceral Or Limb Ischemia">
  <data key="d0">Visceral Or Limb Ischemia</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">A condition caused by aortic branch vessel involvement, classified into dynamic, static, and mixed types, requiring individualized treatment based on symptoms and ischemia degree.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9b35bcbdba3ac4b13dbf19b5e0877</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dynamic Obstruction">
  <data key="d0">Dynamic Obstruction</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A type of branch vessel obstruction that usually resolves spontaneously after proximal tear repair restores true lumen blood flow.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9b35bcbdba3ac4b13dbf19b5e0877</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Static Obstruction">
  <data key="d0">Static Obstruction</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A type of branch vessel obstruction classified by true lumen, false lumen, or dual lumen blood supply, with high severe ischemia risk in false lumen supply patients.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9b35bcbdba3ac4b13dbf19b5e0877</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Chronic TBAD">
  <data key="d0">Chronic TBAD</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A generally stable phase of Type B Aortic Dissection primarily managed with blood pressure control and regular imaging follow-up, with specific surgical intervention indications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a9e9b35bcbdba3ac4b13dbf19b5e0877</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Plaque Or Mural Thrombus Detachment">
  <data key="d0">Plaque Or Mural Thrombus Detachment</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Plaque or mural thrombus detachment is a risk factor associated with stroke.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-591716ddeca1a26bf837c5b70ca9d6db</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Left Vertebral Artery">
  <data key="d0">Left Vertebral Artery</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
  <data key="d2">The left vertebral artery is described as dominant in a specific anatomical context where the left subclavian artery is covered.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-591716ddeca1a26bf837c5b70ca9d6db</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Vagus Vertebral Artery">
  <data key="d0">Vagus Vertebral Artery</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
  <data key="d2">Vagus vertebral artery is listed as a factor related to stroke risk.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-591716ddeca1a26bf837c5b70ca9d6db</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Intraoperative Controlled Hypotension">
  <data key="d0">Intraoperative Controlled Hypotension</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Prolonged intraoperative controlled hypotension is a risk factor associated with both stroke and paraplegia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-591716ddeca1a26bf837c5b70ca9d6db</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Air Embolism">
  <data key="d0">Air Embolism</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Air embolism is a factor related to the risk of stroke.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-591716ddeca1a26bf837c5b70ca9d6db</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cerebral Protection">
  <data key="d0">Cerebral Protection</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Cerebral protection is a necessary measure during operations involving supra-arch branches.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-591716ddeca1a26bf837c5b70ca9d6db</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cerebral Oxygen Monitoring">
  <data key="d0">Cerebral Oxygen Monitoring</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Cerebral oxygen monitoring is a recommended method for brain protection during surgery if conditions permit.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-591716ddeca1a26bf837c5b70ca9d6db</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Paraplegia">
  <data key="d0">Paraplegia</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Paraplegia is a postoperative complication of TEVAR for dissection, characterized by lower limb motor dysfunction.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-591716ddeca1a26bf837c5b70ca9d6db</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cerebrospinal Fluid Pressure Drainage">
  <data key="d0">Cerebrospinal Fluid Pressure Drainage</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) pressure drainage is a treatment for paraplegia, aiming to maintain CSF pressure between 8-10 mmHg.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-591716ddeca1a26bf837c5b70ca9d6db</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mean Arterial Pressure">
  <data key="d0">Mean Arterial Pressure</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Mean arterial pressure is a component in calculating spinal cord perfusion pressure, which is the difference between mean arterial pressure and CSF pressure.&lt;SEP&gt;A hemodynamic parameter that was reduced at baseline and increased under Impella support.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-591716ddeca1a26bf837c5b70ca9d6db&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ace3263be796f5db327b5d6d816ddea2</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;mineru_seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836746</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Anticoagulation">
  <data key="d0">Anticoagulation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Appropriate anticoagulation is a treatment method for paraplegia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-591716ddeca1a26bf837c5b70ca9d6db</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Glucocorticoids">
  <data key="d0">Glucocorticoids</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">Glucocorticoids are among the treatment options for paraplegia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-591716ddeca1a26bf837c5b70ca9d6db</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="T8-L1 Segment">
  <data key="d0">T8-L1 Segment</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
  <data key="d2">The T8-L1 segment is a spinal region from which approximately 75% of great radicular arteries originate; coverage of this segment increases paraplegia risk.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-591716ddeca1a26bf837c5b70ca9d6db</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836585</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Preventive Cerebrospinal Fluid Drainage">
  <data key="d0">Preventive Cerebrospinal Fluid Drainage</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Preventive cerebrospinal fluid drainage is considered preoperatively for patients at high risk of paraplegia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-591716ddeca1a26bf837c5b70ca9d6db</data>
  <data key="d4">Stanford+B+型主动脉夹层诊断和治疗中国专家共识（2022版）.pdf</data>
