<node id="ASS">
  <data key="d0">ASS</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An enzyme whose activity was absent in the liver homogenate and whose deficiency was treated by liver transplantation in a 36-year-old man.&lt;SEP&gt;Argininosuccinate synthetase, a urea cycle enzyme whose deficiency was present in a 36-year-old man treated with liver transplantation; also referred to as AS.&lt;SEP&gt;Argininosuccinate synthetase, a urea cycle enzyme whose activity was absent in the native liver of Patient 2.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d68295a29209c79daf4f790b7e23aa59&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d261ff81dd6e7861a19f6ec0e7ba683d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1325880215e7364fb40c4d244be7ba9</data>
