  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="OTC">
  <data key="d0">OTC</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An enzyme exhibiting significant activity in the liver homogenate; its deficiency was present in six of seven other known patients treated with liver transplantation.&lt;SEP&gt;OTC is a urea cycle enzyme whose activity was normal in the native liver of Patient 1 and exhibited significant activity in Patient 2.&lt;SEP&gt;Ornithine transcarbamylase, a urea cycle enzyme whose deficiency is the most common among patients treated with liver transplantation.&lt;SEP&gt;Ornithine transcarbamylase, a urea cycle enzyme with normal activity in Patient 1 and significant activity in Patient 2.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d68295a29209c79daf4f790b7e23aa59&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-06febe8127a0fccc661f447996c2a367&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d261ff81dd6e7861a19f6ec0e7ba683d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1325880215e7364fb40c4d244be7ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
