</node>
<node id="AS">
  <data key="d0">AS</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An enzyme exhibiting significant activity in the liver homogenate.&lt;SEP&gt;AS is a urea cycle enzyme that exhibited significant activity in the native liver homogenate of Patient 2.&lt;SEP&gt;Argininosuccinate synthetase, a urea cycle enzyme that exhibited significant activity in the discussed context.&lt;SEP&gt;Argininosuccinase, a urea cycle enzyme with significant activity in the native liver of Patient 2.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d68295a29209c79daf4f790b7e23aa59&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-06febe8127a0fccc661f447996c2a367&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d261ff81dd6e7861a19f6ec0e7ba683d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1325880215e7364fb40c4d244be7ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836927</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Urea Cycle Enzyme Deficiency">
  <data key="d0">Urea Cycle Enzyme Deficiency</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A metabolic disorder diagnosed through hyperammonemia and plasma amino acid abnormalities, confirmed by liver analysis, and treated effectively via liver transplantation.&lt;SEP&gt;A group of inborn errors of metabolism affecting the urea cycle, leading to hyperammonemia and plasma amino acid abnormalities.&lt;SEP&gt;Urea cycle enzyme deficiency refers to a group of diseases caused by the lack of enzymes responsible for the biosynthesis of urea from ammonium and glutamine.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d68295a29209c79daf4f790b7e23aa59&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c25934cda6bf6e1490ff5e083ac149ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1325880215e7364fb40c4d244be7ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836927</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hyperammonemia">
  <data key="d0">Hyperammonemia</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A condition of elevated ammonia in the blood, present in both discussed cases, permitting the presumptive diagnosis of urea cycle enzyme deficiency.&lt;SEP&gt;An elevated level of ammonia in the blood, present in both Patient 1 and Patient 2 as a result of their urea cycle enzyme deficiencies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d68295a29209c79daf4f790b7e23aa59&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d261ff81dd6e7861a19f6ec0e7ba683d</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836927</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Plasma Amino Acid Abnormalities">
  <data key="d0">Plasma Amino Acid Abnormalities</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Irregularities in amino acid levels found in patients, aiding in the presumptive diagnosis of urea cycle enzyme deficiency.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d68295a29209c79daf4f790b7e23aa59</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836743</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="2-Wk-Old Infant">
  <data key="d0">2-Wk-Old Infant</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The youngest patient known to undergo successful liver transplantation for CPS-I deficiency.&lt;SEP&gt;The youngest patient known to undergo successful liver transplantation for CPS-I deficiency, who survived for more than 3 years without citrulline supplementation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d68295a29209c79daf4f790b7e23aa59&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1325880215e7364fb40c4d244be7ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836927</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="36-Yr-Old Man">
  <data key="d0">36-Yr-Old Man</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The only patient with ASS deficiency treated thus far with liver transplantation.&lt;SEP&gt;The only patient with ASS deficiency treated with liver transplantation thus far.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d68295a29209c79daf4f790b7e23aa59&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1325880215e7364fb40c4d244be7ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836927</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Liver Transplantation">
  <data key="d0">Liver Transplantation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A surgical procedure that permanently corrects lethal metabolic abnormalities in urea cycle deficiencies, proving more effective than alternative pathways or dietary protein restriction.&lt;SEP&gt;A surgical procedure used to permanently correct lethal metabolic abnormalities in urea cycle enzyme deficiencies, serving as a somatic correction or a step toward enzyme replacement.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d68295a29209c79daf4f790b7e23aa59&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1325880215e7364fb40c4d244be7ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836927</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="20-Mo-Old Boy">
  <data key="d0">20-Mo-Old Boy</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A patient with CPS-I deficiency treated with liver transplantation who had undetectable plasma citrulline postoperatively.&lt;SEP&gt;A patient with CPS-I deficiency treated with liver transplantation who had undetectable plasma citrulline postoperatively, prompting a recommendation for citrulline supplementation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d68295a29209c79daf4f790b7e23aa59&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1325880215e7364fb40c4d244be7ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836928</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Tuchman">
  <data key="d0">Tuchman</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A person who recommended citrulline supplementation postoperatively for the 20-mo-old boy with CPS-I deficiency.&lt;SEP&gt;A person who recommended citrulline supplementation postoperatively for the 20-mo-old boy with CPS-I deficiency.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d68295a29209c79daf4f790b7e23aa59&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1325880215e7364fb40c4d244be7ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836928</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Citrulline Supplementation">
  <data key="d0">Citrulline Supplementation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A treatment recommended by Tuchman for postoperative patients with CPS-I deficiency who have undetectable citrulline.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d68295a29209c79daf4f790b7e23aa59</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836743</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Citrulline">
  <data key="d0">Citrulline</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
  <data key="d2">An amino acid found in the plasma of the 2-wk-old infant, suggesting that in humans it originates in the liver and gut, unlike in rats.&lt;SEP&gt;An amino acid found in human plasma that originates in the liver and gut, unlike in rats; its levels were undetectable in one CPS-I deficient patient but present in another.&lt;SEP&gt;An amino acid that was undetectable in Patient 1 and extremely high in Patient 2 before transplantation, normalizing after OLT.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d68295a29209c79daf4f790b7e23aa59&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d261ff81dd6e7861a19f6ec0e7ba683d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1325880215e7364fb40c4d244be7ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836927</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Plasma Ornithine">
  <data key="d0">Plasma Ornithine</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
  <data key="d2">An amino acid whose level remained slightly high in Patient 2 as late as 20 mo after surgery.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d68295a29209c79daf4f790b7e23aa59</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836743</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Virus-Mediated Transfer Of Human ASS">
  <data key="d0">Virus-Mediated Transfer Of Human ASS</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A gene therapy approach already accomplished in rodents, suggesting the introduction of functional complementary DNA into cells could be a practical therapeutic possibility.&lt;SEP&gt;An experimental therapeutic method accomplished in rodents, suggesting the future possibility of introducing functional complementary DNA into autologous cells.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d68295a29209c79daf4f790b7e23aa59&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1325880215e7364fb40c4d244be7ba9</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836928</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Patient 2">
  <data key="d0">Patient 2</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A patient whose amino acid profile was not completely corrected by liver transplantation, as plasma ornithine levels remained slightly high.&lt;SEP&gt;Patient 2 is a 35-yr-old Japanese man, the second son of healthy first-cousin parents, who had episodes of altered consciousness, was diagnosed with ASS deficiency, and underwent OLT, eventually recovering his neuromotor and intellectual capabilities and returning to his position as a vice president of a construction company.&lt;SEP&gt;Patient 2 is a 35-year-old Japanese man with argininosuccinic acid synthetase deficiency who underwent orthotopic liver transplantation.&lt;SEP&gt;A 35-yr-old Japanese man, the second son of healthy first-cousin parents and father of a healthy daughter, diagnosed with ASS deficiency, who experienced episodes of altered consciousness and coma before undergoing OLT.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d68295a29209c79daf4f790b7e23aa59&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ddddbfb6fedaf71f162814741aeebf51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-06febe8127a0fccc661f447996c2a367&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d261ff81dd6e7861a19f6ec0e7ba683d</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836927</data>
