<node id="Patient 1">
  <data key="d0">Patient 1</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Patient 1 is a 2-wk-old infant who experienced severe rejection postoperatively, an Aspergillus brain abscess, bacteremia, and systemic cytomegalovirus infection, but subsequently lived at home with normal growth and weight gain, though with delayed physical and intellectual milestones.&lt;SEP&gt;Patient 1 is a 14-day-old white boy with carbamyl phosphate synthetase-I deficiency who underwent orthotopic liver transplantation and experienced an Aspergillus brain abscess post-surgery.&lt;SEP&gt;A 2-wk-old infant with CPS-I deficiency, the youngest known patient with this condition, who suffered from an Aspergillus brain abscess, bacteremia, and systemic cytomegalovirus infection, and underwent OLT.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ddddbfb6fedaf71f162814741aeebf51&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-06febe8127a0fccc661f447996c2a367&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d261ff81dd6e7861a19f6ec0e7ba683d</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836927</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
