  <data key="d5">1779836927</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Aspergillus Brain Abscess">
  <data key="d0">Aspergillus Brain Abscess</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">An Aspergillus brain abscess in Patient 1 was treated successfully with antibiotics, open drainage, and a ventriculoperitoneal shunt.&lt;SEP&gt;A medical complication in Patient 1 treated successfully with antibiotics, open drainage, and a ventriculoperitoneal shunt, which caused cortical injury.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-06febe8127a0fccc661f447996c2a367&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d261ff81dd6e7861a19f6ec0e7ba683d</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836927</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="OKT3">
  <data key="d0">OKT3</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">OKT3 was added to the treatment regimen of Patient 1 to manage severe rejection beginning in postoperative week 3.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-06febe8127a0fccc661f447996c2a367</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836743</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ASS Deficiency">
  <data key="d0">ASS Deficiency</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">ASS deficiency is a urea cycle enzyme deficiency diagnosed in Patient 2, characterized by elevated serum ammonium and citrulline levels.&lt;SEP&gt;A urea cycle enzyme deficiency characterized by the absence of ASS activity in the liver, leading to hyperammonemia, extremely high citrulline levels, and episodes of altered consciousness and coma.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-06febe8127a0fccc661f447996c2a367&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d261ff81dd6e7861a19f6ec0e7ba683d</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836927</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="OLT">
  <data key="d0">OLT</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Orthotopic liver transplantation (OLT) is the surgical procedure performed on both Patient 1 and Patient 2 to treat their urea cycle enzyme deficiencies.&lt;SEP&gt;Orthotopic liver transplantation, a surgical procedure performed on both Patient 1 and Patient 2 to treat their respective urea cycle enzyme deficiencies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-06febe8127a0fccc661f447996c2a367&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d261ff81dd6e7861a19f6ec0e7ba683d</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836927</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cyclosporine-Steroid Therapy">
  <data key="d0">Cyclosporine-Steroid Therapy</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Cyclosporine-steroid therapy was used for Patient 2 postoperatively, resulting in uncomplicated convalescence.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-06febe8127a0fccc661f447996c2a367</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836743</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Yale University School of Medicine">
  <data key="d0">Yale University School of Medicine</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Yale University School of Medicine is the institution where CPS-I and OTC were measured in Patient 1.&lt;SEP&gt;An institution whose Department of Human Genetics measured CPS-I and OTC in Patient 1.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-06febe8127a0fccc661f447996c2a367&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d261ff81dd6e7861a19f6ec0e7ba683d</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836927</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="CPS-I">
  <data key="d0">CPS-I</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">CPS-I is a urea cycle enzyme whose activity was undetectable in the native liver homogenate of Patient 1.&lt;SEP&gt;Carbamoyl phosphate synthetase I, a urea cycle enzyme whose activity was undetectable in the native liver of Patient 1.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-06febe8127a0fccc661f447996c2a367&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d261ff81dd6e7861a19f6ec0e7ba683d</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_todo1992.pdf&lt;SEP&gt;todo1992.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836927</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="SHOCK Trial">
  <data key="d0">SHOCK Trial</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">A clinical trial where clinical and hemodynamic criteria were previously described.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ace3263be796f5db327b5d6d816ddea2</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836746</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Impella LP2.5">
  <data key="d0">Impella LP2.5</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A percutaneous left ventricular assist device with a maximal pump flow of 2.5 L/min, used for hemodynamic support in patients with cardiogenic shock.&lt;SEP&gt;A catheter-based, impeller-driven, axial-flow left ventricular assist device (LVAD) with a maximal flow of 2.5 l/min, implanted via a percutaneous approach to provide hemodynamic support.&lt;SEP&gt;Impella LP2.5 is a catheter-based, miniaturized rotary blood pump that increased Cardiac Index, cardiac output, and Mean Arterial Pressure 30 min after implantation.&lt;SEP&gt;A catheter-based miniaturized rotary blood pump and percutaneous transvalvular LVAD that aspirates blood from the left ventricle and expels it to the ascending aorta with a maximal flow of 2.5 l/min.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ace3263be796f5db327b5d6d816ddea2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ca971059e15553c9f065f9d48ca96130&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d070016888b87e5d8407655292c6a98&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40ef920a3d882cbe9feb69d377f883e2</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836746</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="IABP">
  <data key="d0">IABP</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">IABP (Intra-Aortic Balloon Pump) is a mechanical support device compared against Impella, associated with longer mechanical ventilation time and a significant reduction in Diastolic Arterial Pressure (DAP).&lt;SEP&gt;Intra-aortic balloon pump, used as a comparison device against the Impella LP2.5 in the study.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ace3263be796f5db327b5d6d816ddea2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d070016888b87e5d8407655292c6a98</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836746</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cardiac Index">
  <data key="d0">Cardiac Index</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A hemodynamic parameter used as the primary end point in the study, measured from baseline to 30 min after device implantation.&lt;SEP&gt;A hemodynamic parameter used as the primary end point of the study, defined as the change from baseline at 30 min after implantation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ace3263be796f5db327b5d6d816ddea2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40ef920a3d882cbe9feb69d377f883e2</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836746</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Multiple Organ Dysfunction Score">
  <data key="d0">Multiple Organ Dysfunction Score</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A scoring criteria used to evaluate multiple-organ dysfunction at 30 days.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ace3263be796f5db327b5d6d816ddea2</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836746</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sepsis-related Organ Failure Assessment">
  <data key="d0">Sepsis-related Organ Failure Assessment</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A criteria used to evaluate organ failure and dysfunction scores at 30 days.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ace3263be796f5db327b5d6d816ddea2</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836746</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cardiac Power Index">
  <data key="d0">Cardiac Power Index</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">A calculated metric defined as Cardiac Index multiplied by mean arterial pressure multiplied by 0.0022.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ace3263be796f5db327b5d6d816ddea2</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836746</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Diastolic Arterial Pressure">
  <data key="d0">Diastolic Arterial Pressure</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">A hemodynamic parameter that showed the greatest difference between the Impella and IABP groups, increasing under Impella support.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ace3263be796f5db327b5d6d816ddea2</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836746</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Serum Lactate">
  <data key="d0">Serum Lactate</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">A metabolic parameter that was lower in patients treated with Impella during the first 48 hours.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ace3263be796f5db327b5d6d816ddea2</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836746</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Epinephrine">
  <data key="d0">Epinephrine</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Epinephrine is a vasopressor agent used during the first 24 hours of treatment, with similar overall doses administered in both the Impella and IABP groups.&lt;SEP&gt;A vasopressor agent administered in similar overall doses to both the Impella and IABP groups during the first 24 hours.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ace3263be796f5db327b5d6d816ddea2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d070016888b87e5d8407655292c6a98</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836746</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Intra-Aortic Balloon Pump">
  <data key="d0">Intra-Aortic Balloon Pump</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A standard counterpulsation device used for hemodynamic support in patients with cardiogenic shock.&lt;SEP&gt;A standard medical device used for counterpulsation therapy to provide hemodynamic support in cardiogenic shock, though with limited hemodynamic benefits.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ca971059e15553c9f065f9d48ca96130&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40ef920a3d882cbe9feb69d377f883e2</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836746</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="MODS">
  <data key="d0">MODS</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Multiple Organ Dysfunction Score, used to evaluate organ dysfunction at baseline and 30 days.&lt;SEP&gt;MODS (Multiple Organ Dysfunction Score) is a criteria used to evaluate overall outcome and complex organ dysfunction, which showed significant improvement in both treatment arms after 30 days.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ca971059e15553c9f065f9d48ca96130&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d070016888b87e5d8407655292c6a98</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836746</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="SOFA">
  <data key="d0">SOFA</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Sepsis-related Organ Failure Assessment score, used to evaluate organ failure at baseline and 30 days.&lt;SEP&gt;SOFA is a criteria used to evaluate overall outcome and complex organ dysfunction, which showed significant improvement in both treatment arms after 30 days.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ca971059e15553c9f065f9d48ca96130&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d070016888b87e5d8407655292c6a98</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836746</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cardiogenic Shock">
  <data key="d0">Cardiogenic Shock</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A condition of inadequate cardiac output leading to tissue hypoperfusion, often caused by acute myocardial infarction.&lt;SEP&gt;A severe medical condition affecting 6% to 8% of patients with acute myocardial infarction, associated with a high mortality rate of 40% to 50%.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ca971059e15553c9f065f9d48ca96130&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40ef920a3d882cbe9feb69d377f883e2</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836746</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Acute Myocardial Infarction">
  <data key="d0">Acute Myocardial Infarction</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A heart attack, a major cause of cardiogenic shock.&lt;SEP&gt;A medical event causing left ventricular failure, which can lead to cardiogenic shock and high mortality.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ca971059e15553c9f065f9d48ca96130&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-40ef920a3d882cbe9feb69d377f883e2</data>
  <data key="d4">mineru_seyfarth2008.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779836746</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
