<node id="Jiang Yuxin">
  <data key="d0">Jiang Yuxin</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">A corresponding author of the Chinese expert consensus on sonographic evaluation of endometriosis.&lt;SEP&gt;Jiang Yuxin is the head of the Consensus Writing Group and a core expert from Peking Union Medical College Hospital.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09381648ecd5917039e244d62da638ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8cbe0f288d4aaea04ac19b92c24f1266</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837098</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Endometriosis">
  <data key="d0">Endometriosis</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A chronic disease in women of childbearing age where endometrial tissue appears outside the uterine body, commonly causing pain and infertility.&lt;SEP&gt;Endometriosis is a condition often accompanied by pelvic adhesions, requiring systematic ultrasound evaluation for diagnosis and severity assessment.&lt;SEP&gt;Endometriosis is a condition with widespread, morphologically diverse, invasive, and recurrent lesions that can coexist in multiple pelvic locations.&lt;SEP&gt;Endometriosis is a condition requiring early diagnosis, clinical treatment, and follow-up, supported by comprehensive ultrasound evaluation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09381648ecd5917039e244d62da638ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1afac1628b13e9e616403ae39f70ecbe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-61317a57efdf6bb9fc1bcf3ec62ff924&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8cbe0f288d4aaea04ac19b92c24f1266</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837098</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ovarian Endometriosis">
  <data key="d0">Ovarian Endometriosis</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Also known as ovarian endometriotic cyst or chocolate cyst, it is the most common type of endometriosis.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09381648ecd5917039e244d62da638ee</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837098</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Peritoneal Endometriosis">
  <data key="d0">Peritoneal Endometriosis</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A type of endometriosis involving superficial endometriosis implants on the pelvic peritoneum, usually diagnosed by laparoscopy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09381648ecd5917039e244d62da638ee</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837098</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Deep Infiltrating Endometriosis">
  <data key="d0">Deep Infiltrating Endometriosis</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A type of endometriosis where lesions infiltrate deeper than 5mm, affecting areas like uterosacral ligaments, rectovaginal septum, and bowel.&lt;SEP&gt;A form of endometriosis that infiltrates pelvic structures, often coexisting with ovarian endometriosis, requiring comprehensive ultrasound evaluation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09381648ecd5917039e244d62da638ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0dd3aace07e5e2f67f60579de0b36b76</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837098</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Other Site Endometriosis">
  <data key="d0">Other Site Endometriosis</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Endometriosis occurring in other locations, including scar endometriosis and other rare distant endometriosis.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09381648ecd5917039e244d62da638ee</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837098</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Transvaginal Ultrasound">
  <data key="d0">Transvaginal Ultrasound</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The preferred ultrasound examination approach for endometriosis, especially for suspected deep infiltrating endometriosis and small ovarian cysts.&lt;SEP&gt;Transvaginal ultrasound is a specific ultrasound method with an overall sensitivity of 78.5-85.3% and specificity of 46.1-92.5% for detecting endometriosis lesions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09381648ecd5917039e244d62da638ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-61317a57efdf6bb9fc1bcf3ec62ff924</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837098</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Transrectal Ultrasound">
  <data key="d0">Transrectal Ultrasound</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">An alternative ultrasound examination approach for patients who cannot undergo transvaginal ultrasound.&lt;SEP&gt;Transrectal ultrasound is an examination approach that requires preparation consistent with transvaginal ultrasound or simple bowel preparation to obtain clearer images, utilizing dual-plane probes and rectal 360 intracavitary high-frequency probes to detect bowel wall lesions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09381648ecd5917039e244d62da638ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1afac1628b13e9e616403ae39f70ecbe</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837098</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Tenderness-Guided Method">
  <data key="d0">Tenderness-Guided Method</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Tenderness-guided method is an auxiliary scanning technique where the operator observes the patient's pain response during probe movement or light pressure on clinically tender areas to carefully search for lesions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1afac1628b13e9e616403ae39f70ecbe</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Saline Or Gel Ultrasound Imaging">
  <data key="d0">Saline Or Gel Ultrasound Imaging</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Saline or gel ultrasound imaging is an auxiliary technique involving the injection of normal saline or gel into the vagina or rectum during ultrasound to help observe lesions on the vaginal wall, anterior/posterior vaginal fornices, or rectal wall.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1afac1628b13e9e616403ae39f70ecbe</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pre-Examination Bowel Preparation">
  <data key="d0">Pre-Examination Bowel Preparation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Pre-examination bowel preparation is an auxiliary technique performed before the examination to help detect lesions in the rectum and sigmoid colon.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1afac1628b13e9e616403ae39f70ecbe</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Uterine Sliding Sign Examination Method">
  <data key="d0">Uterine Sliding Sign Examination Method</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Uterine sliding sign examination method is an easy-to-master ultrasound technique used to check whether the pouch of Douglas is obliterated, by observing the relative movement between the cervix/uterus and the anterior rectal wall when lightly pushing with a probe.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1afac1628b13e9e616403ae39f70ecbe</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pouch Of Douglas">
  <data key="d0">Pouch Of Douglas</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The pouch of Douglas is a pelvic space whose obliteration is assessed using the uterine sliding sign.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1afac1628b13e9e616403ae39f70ecbe</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pelvic Adhesions">
  <data key="d0">Pelvic Adhesions</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Pelvic adhesions are frequently associated with endometriosis, evaluated via ultrasound by observing relative movement between organs, uterine sliding sign, and indirect signs like localized fluid or hydrosalpinx.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1afac1628b13e9e616403ae39f70ecbe</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Consensus">
  <data key="d0">Consensus</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">The Consensus provides recommendations for evaluating suspected endometriosis patients, including inquiring about medical history, using intracavitary high-frequency probes, applying tenderness-guided methods, and performing a 3-step systematic ultrasound evaluation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1afac1628b13e9e616403ae39f70ecbe</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Systematic Ultrasound Evaluation">
  <data key="d0">Systematic Ultrasound Evaluation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Systematic ultrasound evaluation is a 3-step diagnostic procedure recommended for patients with suspected endometriosis.&lt;SEP&gt;Systematic ultrasound evaluation for endometriosis consists of three steps: standard examination from the vaginal median sagittal plane, searching for suspected lesions in the anterior and posterior pelvis, and observing ovarian mobility and uterine sliding sign to assess adhesions and obliteration.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1afac1628b13e9e616403ae39f70ecbe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48130c78d9e3e6001f4b2909ff14d577</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ovarian Endometriotic Cyst">
  <data key="d0">Ovarian Endometriotic Cyst</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Ovarian endometriotic cyst is a manifestation of endometriosis characterized by specific ultrasound features such as ground-glass echotexture, thick or uneven walls, and lack of internal blood flow.&lt;SEP&gt;Ovarian endometriotic cyst is a lesion with typical ultrasound features, including a "ground-glass" echogenicity of the cyst contents.&lt;SEP&gt;Ovarian endometriotic cyst is a lesion characterized by layered echogenicity, "ground-glass" echogenicity, and relatively thick cyst walls, which can undergo decidualization during pregnancy.&lt;SEP&gt;Ovarian endometriotic cyst is a condition that presents diagnostic challenges, particularly for atypical manifestations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1afac1628b13e9e616403ae39f70ecbe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-61317a57efdf6bb9fc1bcf3ec62ff924&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8cbe0f288d4aaea04ac19b92c24f1266&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48130c78d9e3e6001f4b2909ff14d577</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dual-Plane Probe">
  <data key="d0">Dual-Plane Probe</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Dual-plane probe is a type of ultrasound equipment used in transrectal examinations to help detect bowel wall lesions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1afac1628b13e9e616403ae39f70ecbe</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Rectal 360 Intracavitary High-Frequency Probe">
  <data key="d0">Rectal 360 Intracavitary High-Frequency Probe</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Rectal 360 intracavitary high-frequency probe is a type of ultrasound equipment used in transrectal examinations to help detect bowel wall lesions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1afac1628b13e9e616403ae39f70ecbe</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Blood Clot">
  <data key="d0">Blood Clot</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
  <data key="d2">Blood clots form inside ovarian endometriotic cysts and need to be differentiated from papillary structures and solid lesions of ovarian tumors.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-61317a57efdf6bb9fc1bcf3ec62ff924</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ovarian Epithelial Tumor">
  <data key="d0">Ovarian Epithelial Tumor</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An ovarian tumor with papillary or solid lesions that must be differentiated from blood clots within an ovarian endometrioma.&lt;SEP&gt;Ovarian epithelial tumors contain papillary structures and solid lesions that typically exhibit blood flow signals, especially in borderline or malignant cases.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-61317a57efdf6bb9fc1bcf3ec62ff924&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0dd3aace07e5e2f67f60579de0b36b76</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ovarian Mucinous Epithelial Tumor">
  <data key="d0">Ovarian Mucinous Epithelial Tumor</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Ovarian mucinous epithelial tumors have sonographic features that significantly overlap with multilocular ovarian endometriotic cysts, making differentiation difficult.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-61317a57efdf6bb9fc1bcf3ec62ff924</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pelvic Abscess">
  <data key="d0">Pelvic Abscess</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A pelvic infection collection that needs to be differentiated from an ovarian endometrioma.&lt;SEP&gt;Pelvic abscess presents with acute infection symptoms like fever and lower abdominal pain, and sonographically shows unevenly thickened walls and tubular structures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-61317a57efdf6bb9fc1bcf3ec62ff924&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0dd3aace07e5e2f67f60579de0b36b76</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Bladder Cancer">
  <data key="d0">Bladder Cancer</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A malignant tumor of the bladder that must be differentiated from bladder endometriosis.&lt;SEP&gt;Bladder cancer is a malignant tumor located in the mucosal layer, growing papillary or cauliflower-like into the lumen, and invading the full wall layer only in late stages.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-61317a57efdf6bb9fc1bcf3ec62ff924&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0dd3aace07e5e2f67f60579de0b36b76</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Rectal Cancer">
  <data key="d0">Rectal Cancer</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A malignant tumor of the rectum that must be differentiated from rectal endometriosis.&lt;SEP&gt;Rectal cancer is a malignant tumor located in the mucosal layer, growing papillary or cauliflower-like into the lumen, and invading the full wall layer only in late stages.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-61317a57efdf6bb9fc1bcf3ec62ff924&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0dd3aace07e5e2f67f60579de0b36b76</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ultrasound">
  <data key="d0">Ultrasound</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Ultrasound is the preferred non-invasive imaging method for endometriosis, possessing specific sonographic characteristics but having limitations in detecting small or deeply located lesions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-61317a57efdf6bb9fc1bcf3ec62ff924</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Contrast-Enhanced Ultrasound">
  <data key="d0">Contrast-Enhanced Ultrasound</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Contrast-enhanced ultrasound is utilized to assist in clear diagnosis when differentiating blood clots from ovarian tumor solid lesions is difficult.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-61317a57efdf6bb9fc1bcf3ec62ff924</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Rectum">
  <data key="d0">Rectum</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The rectum is a location where endometriosis can occur, with an ultrasound detection sensitivity of 33.3-98.1% and specificity of 86-100%.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-61317a57efdf6bb9fc1bcf3ec62ff924</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sigmoid Colon">
  <data key="d0">Sigmoid Colon</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The sigmoid colon is a location where endometriosis can occur, sharing detection rates with the rectum.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-61317a57efdf6bb9fc1bcf3ec62ff924</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Uterosacral Ligament">
  <data key="d0">Uterosacral Ligament</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Uterosacral ligament is one of the most commonly affected sites by endometriosis, often bilaterally, appearing as poorly defined hypoechoic nodules or strip-like hypoechoic areas on ultrasound.&lt;SEP&gt;The uterosacral ligament is a deeply located endometriosis site with a low ultrasound detection sensitivity of 10-88.9% and specificity of 75-99.6%.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-61317a57efdf6bb9fc1bcf3ec62ff924&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48130c78d9e3e6001f4b2909ff14d577</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Rectovaginal Septum">
  <data key="d0">Rectovaginal Septum</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The region between the posterior vaginal wall and the anterior rectal wall, extending from the level of the posterior lip of the cervix to the vaginal orifice.&lt;SEP&gt;Rectovaginal septum is the area between the posterior vaginal wall and anterior rectal wall; endometriosis here is indicated by lesions below the posterior lip of the cervix, appearing as nodular, elongated, or irregular hypoechoic structures.&lt;SEP&gt;The rectovaginal septum is a deeply located endometriosis site with an ultrasound detection sensitivity of 36-62% and specificity of 95-99%.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-61317a57efdf6bb9fc1bcf3ec62ff924&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-48130c78d9e3e6001f4b2909ff14d577&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0dd3aace07e5e2f67f60579de0b36b76</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ultrasound Examination">
  <data key="d0">Ultrasound Examination</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Ultrasound examination is a diagnostic method for suspected endometriosis that should be combined with clinical history, symptoms, and signs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8cbe0f288d4aaea04ac19b92c24f1266</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Consensus Writing Group">
  <data key="d0">Consensus Writing Group</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Consensus Writing Group is an organization responsible for drafting the medical consensus, led by Jiang Yuxin, Tian Jiawei, and Wu Qingqing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8cbe0f288d4aaea04ac19b92c24f1266</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
