</node>
<node id="The First Medical Center of Chinese PLA General Hospital">
  <data key="d0">The First Medical Center of Chinese PLA General Hospital</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The First Medical Center of</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8cbe0f288d4aaea04ac19b92c24f1266</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ground-Glass Echotexture">
  <data key="d0">Ground-Glass Echotexture</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Ground-glass echotexture is a typical ultrasound feature of ovarian endometriotic cysts, described as homogeneous dense punctate echoes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-48130c78d9e3e6001f4b2909ff14d577</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Color Doppler Flow Imaging">
  <data key="d0">Color Doppler Flow Imaging</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Color Doppler flow imaging is an ultrasound technique used to assess blood flow, showing no internal signals in ovarian endometriotic cysts but strip-like signals on the wall or septa.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-48130c78d9e3e6001f4b2909ff14d577</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Old Blood Or Blood Clot">
  <data key="d0">Old Blood Or Blood Clot</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalobject</data>
  <data key="d2">Old blood or blood clots within ovarian endometriotic cysts appear on ultrasound as irregular cloud-like medium echoes or mass-like medium-high echoes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-48130c78d9e3e6001f4b2909ff14d577</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Decidualization">
  <data key="d0">Decidualization</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Decidualization occurs in about 40% of ovarian endometriotic cyst walls during pregnancy, presenting as significantly thickened walls with regular papillary projections and abundant blood flow.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-48130c78d9e3e6001f4b2909ff14d577</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Malignant Transformation Of Endometriosis">
  <data key="d0">Malignant Transformation Of Endometriosis</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Malignant transformation of endometriosis is suspected when an ovarian endometriotic cyst significantly enlarges, develops solid echogenic structures with abundant blood flow, or grows post-menopause.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-48130c78d9e3e6001f4b2909ff14d577</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Bladder Endometriosis">
  <data key="d0">Bladder Endometriosis</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Bladder endometriosis presents as hypoechoic nodular or irregular lesions within the bladder wall, typically at the posterior wall midline, rarely involving the mucosa.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-48130c78d9e3e6001f4b2909ff14d577</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837099</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ureteral Endometriosis">
  <data key="d0">Ureteral Endometriosis</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Ureteral endometriosis is mostly caused by posterior pelvic lesions like uterosacral ligament involvement, leading to ureteral obstruction and potentially severe hydronephrosis and impaired renal function.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-48130c78d9e3e6001f4b2909ff14d577</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837100</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Rectouterine Pouch">
  <data key="d0">Rectouterine Pouch</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Rectouterine pouch is located behind the cervix and above the rectovaginal septum, frequently affected by endometriosis, showing poorly defined lesions and negative uterine sliding sign.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-48130c78d9e3e6001f4b2909ff14d577</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837100</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Intestine">
  <data key="d0">Intestine</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The intestinal tract, specifically the rectum and sigmoid colon, which are commonly affected by endometriosis lesions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dd3aace07e5e2f67f60579de0b36b76</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837100</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Scar Endometriosis">
  <data key="d0">Scar Endometriosis</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Endometriosis occurring within surgical scars, primarily from cesarean section incisions or perineal lacerations/episiotomies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dd3aace07e5e2f67f60579de0b36b76</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837100</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ovarian Endometrioma">
  <data key="d0">Ovarian Endometrioma</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An ovarian cyst filled with old blood, also known as a chocolate cyst, which requires differentiation from other ovarian masses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dd3aace07e5e2f67f60579de0b36b76</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837100</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ultrasound Evaluation">
  <data key="d0">Ultrasound Evaluation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">A diagnostic imaging method used to assess endometriosis lesions, their characteristics, pelvic adhesions, and hydronephrosis.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dd3aace07e5e2f67f60579de0b36b76</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837100</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Posterior Cervical Region">
  <data key="d0">Posterior Cervical Region</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">A common site for deep infiltrating endometriosis, including the uterosacral ligaments.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dd3aace07e5e2f67f60579de0b36b76</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837100</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cesarean Section Scar">
  <data key="d0">Cesarean Section Scar</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">An abdominal wall incision scar where endometriosis can develop within the subcutaneous fat and/or muscle layers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dd3aace07e5e2f67f60579de0b36b76</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837100</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Perineal Scar">
  <data key="d0">Perineal Scar</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">A scar from a perineal laceration or episiotomy where endometriosis can develop within subcutaneous fat and/or muscle layers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dd3aace07e5e2f67f60579de0b36b76</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837100</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ovarian Hemorrhagic Cyst">
  <data key="d0">Ovarian Hemorrhagic Cyst</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A type of ovarian cyst characterized by reticular, cord-like, or uneven point-like echoes, used as a differential diagnosis for ovarian endometriomas.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dd3aace07e5e2f67f60579de0b36b76</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837100</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dermoid Cyst">
  <data key="d0">Dermoid Cyst</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A type of ovarian tumor exhibiting a fat-fluid level sign, requiring differentiation from the layered sign of an endometrioma.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0dd3aace07e5e2f67f60579de0b36b76</data>
  <data key="d4">子宫内膜异位症超声评估中国专家共识.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1779837100</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
